                     IFeatureCollection<IRoadLine> roads,

                     StreetNetworkCriterionSet criteria)
        Constructor from the outline of the city being the street network, the criteria for aggregation, some parameters of the algorithm and all the feature collections needed (roads, strokes, roundabouts and branching crossroads and blocks).
        Parameters:
        geom - the outline of the street network (of the city)
        roads - all the roads of the data being generalised
        strokes - all the strokes of the data being generalised
        roundabouts - all the roundabouts of the data being generalised
        branchings - all the branchings of the data being generalised
        blocks - all the blocks of the data being generalised
        criteria - an object containing the criteria used (each being true or false)

      • setAggregationCriteria

        public void setAggregationCriteria(boolean compact,
                                   boolean area,
                                   boolean strokes,
                                   boolean traffic,
                                   boolean centrality,
                                   boolean building,
                                   boolean density,
                                   boolean crossing)
        Set the criteria used in the aggregation cost function.
        Parameters:
        compact - true to use the block compactness criterion
        area - true to use the block size criterion
        strokes - true to use the strokes length criterion
        traffic - true to use the traffic estimation criterion
        centrality - true to use the stroke dual centrality criterion
        building - true to use the building density criterion
        density - true to use the block density criterion
        crossing - true to use the partition crossing criterion

      • limitedAggregationAlgorithm

        public void limitedAggregationAlgorithm()

        Core of the street selection algorithm by block aggregation : the city block are aggregated according to t-Gap principle thanks to cost function. This version of the algorithm uses the dynamics for Anne Ruas' PhD: only one aggregation is allowed per city block.

      • aggregationAlgorithm

        public void aggregationAlgorithm()

        Core of the street selection algorithm by block aggregation : the city block are aggregated according to t-Gap principle thanks to cost function. This version of the algorithm uses the dynamics proposed by (Touya, 2007) road selection algorithm: multiple aggregations are allowed as long as the cost is less than max cost for the city.
